name: The Yani Hotel Bali
address: Jalan Bypass Ngurah Rai.660 Pedungan, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80222, Indonesia
review 1: Do not stay here! So dirty, the room was so discusting. The sheets were not clean and had hole in them, the towels used to be white but were now brown-grey. We took one looked and checked out directly and booked another hotel. In the taxi the driver told us it is known for being haunted. I regret not taking pictures too prove this but we could not get out of there fast enough!
review 2: Do not book. The pictures lie. This was the most disgusting room I've been in. Stains on the curtains, bedcovers and sheets. Didn't even want to sit on the bed. Brownish colored bathtowels. Was there for about 5 minutes before we decided to get another hotel. The taxi driver to our new hotel said it also was famous for being haunted. No pictures cus we litterly ran out of there.
review 3:
I stayed here from October 9th until October 14th for business trip.

The room was quite spacious, with one refrigerator.
Unfortunately, the room where I stayed have no dress cabinet, but that was not an issue to me.
The bathroom was equipped with soap dispensers, which is good thing, most hotel would place soap bar

The TV was showing cable channel and the AC was working fine .. too bad during my stays, I have fever, therefor I cannot stand cold air ;)

This hotel also have swimming pools, not big, but it is nice.

The staff are also very helpful.

Location of Hotel is not on center of denpasar, but rather to the south of Denpasar, between Kuta Beach and Sanur Beach, but you can go anywhere from here ;)

If I come to Bali again with my family, I would stay in here again.
review 4:
Budget hotel with satisfactory service.

I've stayed in this hotel for 3 days since 27 to 30 Dec 2018 on second floor. No stink and rats as what they told in other review, just barking dog noise from neighbourhood area.

Breakfast is nice in terms of taste, but don't expect much in terms of variety. They only serve fruit/veg salad, white rice, fried rice, veg dish, meat dish, bread, sliced fruit, tea, coffee and juice.

The only downside is it's location isn't strategic enough if you don't rent or come with your own vehicle, quite far from anywhere expect the airport.
review 5:
Expensive smelly hotel.
This place reeks of rotting trash from the nearby trash collection point. Rooms and corridors are old and not well-maintained. The air-conditioner vibrates and is noisy as hell. Worst possible hotel you can get at Rp 550k price point.

name: Warung lomie
address: Jl. Diponegoro No.17, Pedungan, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80222, Indonesia
review 1:
Mie Kacang is my favorit dish so far, but the noodle curry is delicious as well. Lomie is good too but the herbs taste quite strong.

Food and drink price is cheap, you can park on the road side but be careful due to a very busy road during the day.

The place is quite small, maybe only can cater around 20 people.
review 2:
SO DELICIOUS.
GENUINE Chinese RIAU cuisine.
So good. The broth of lomie you can smell taste n feel the cloves n herbs. Very good. Very delicious
review 3: Authentic noodle waroeng. Its a small waroeng but Recommend to find chinese cuisine tasty noodles. It has very limited parking  area.
review 4: Try Mie Kare for 25k. It was worth the price for me. Just expecting bigger portion lol.  Atmosphere really kinda of authentic Street Noodle  restaurant. The condiments like chili pickle and sambal really works to elevate the flavour.
review 5: Have patronised this for quite some time, the mie kacang and pangsit is superb. Dad often buy it for breakfast and our background is from selatpanjangü´£

name: Nira Guest House Sanur, Bali
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai No.5, Sanur, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80222, Indonesia
review 1: Lovely room. You have to walk all the way through the furniture shop to the back. I just stayed before my flight (and left in the night). They actually didn't have a record of my booking but were very happy with my email confirmation. Bathroom wasn't the cleanest. Less than 20 minutes to the airport.
review 2:
This ONE is Nira guest house, not the one east, near Sanur beach! 2 Google entries!
Apart from that, it's the cleanest and most extraordinary guesthouse I've encountered on Bali. Amazing design! The hotel is located inside an art gallery and the rooms are equipped with wonderful  balinese artwork furniture. Super clean and completely new renovated. The pool was the cleanest I've seen on my 3 weeks Indonesia trip and the hosts were super friendly and supportive. Strongly recommended!! üëçüëçüëçüëç

name: Warung Sederhana Bojonegoro "Bu Pasmi"
address: Jalan Diponegoro No.83, Pesanggaran,Pedungan, Pedungan, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80222, Indonesia
review 1: It's a traditional East Javanese warung located in Pedungan, Denpasar city. Their main course in Fish head (snapper) soup. Taste is good and fresh if you love sea food. Other menus are available with reasonable price. Most of the fish menus are coming in big size compared with others.
review 2: This place is a hidden gem. The traditional recipe fish head soup is to die for. Consider very cheap too. No need too much words. Must try.
review 3: They have a local menu with Javanese style and the famous one are head fish soup with local ingredients. Taste are fresh and fish are very fresh , little bit spicy . Price are acceptable and a lot of food choices. Good service and fast response , remember they only have 2-3 space for car parking so come earlier it's better
review 4: No covid-19 protocol ini here because the seller doesn't wear mask (by the time i dine in) and there is no social distance table if you dine in too. But the food is soooooo goooood! The fish head is really delicious üëçüèºüëçüèºüëçüèº
review 5:
One of the best Sup Kepala Ikan in Bali. There are also other menu available.
The place is ok but it could be better

name: "Sari Nadi" Suckling Pig Warung
address: Jl. Diponegoro No.747, Pedungan, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80222, Indonesia
review 1:
The food itself is five star. One of the best I've had in Bali (and trust me I've had quite a bit). Be careful with the soup because that's where the heat is, not super spicy but if you're thinking of diluting the heat with the soup you're in for a surprise. They have various kinds of meat in the meal, each of them tasty.

Unfortunately it's situated in a place where the air (within several kms radius) smells of death and decay.
review 2: Very crispy pork skin, especially when you come here for breakfast.
review 3: Traditional suckling pig. They open from early in the morning so if you want to eat suckling pig for your breakfast then you definitely have to come to this place.
review 4: The nasi campur (Balinese tradisional mixed rice) here is very delicious! With a reasonable price! A must try...
review 5: Food was moderate... nothing special.. expected to be more flavourful . Bland instead

name: Warung Amla
address: Jl. Diponegoro, Pedungan, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80222, Indonesia
review 1: The place is quite cozy and the food taste good. Kolobak, Capcay, and Puyunghai taste very good.
review 2: To be honest the taste was not really good. Compare with the prices it was not worth yo buy. No taste at all and too expensive. Honest review, better to improve the food and service as well
review 3: the food is absolutely good , but the waitress are not really friendly üôÑ
review 4: Balinese cuisine, many options and most of them are delicious, a bit crowded at lunch time, and if you love sambal...this place has the best fresh sambal to be paired with their foods, it's almost addicting haha
review 5: Delicious Food right here, the price is not expensive, and dishes within 10-20 minutes depends on your order. If you're forbidden to eat pork, please do not come here.

review 2: Service not god, because the employee no smile and the face indifferent

name: Warung Rujak Ambengan
address: Jl. Diponegoro No.31, Pedungan, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80222, Indonesia
review 1:
5 stars for the taste of food, but 3 stars for convenience as the place is very small/cramped. Not a lot of space to seat & often crowded. It's located exactly near a big road so dust is guaranteed. Plus for GoFood order, location is a bit misleading, it says location on jalan Diponegoro while it's actually located on Jalan Raya Sesetan.
Therefore I give 4 stars, somewhere in the middle.
The place is not really easy to find, so watch out for Banjar Ambengan, it's located exactly opposite the Banjar.
review 2: Almost all of the food here are delicious, worth to try üëç
review 4: My wife favorite food in Bali

review 1:
It's super dirty and the sort of place where you know you'll get sick. But, the soto is very authentic and I really enjoyed it after a couple of hours of wakeboarding.

Try it if you're in the area
review 2: Great ambiance, nice atmoshpere, photogenic, and nice espresso. Defenitelly would bring my wife and his boyfriend to this place.
review 3:
This place offers one of the best Soto in Denpasar.
They also have duck.
The location is right at a busy junction so it may be hard to get if you're driving from the west.
Overall 2 thumbs-up üëçüëç
review 4: This is a old traditional soto restaurant that should be a must do in Bali the food is exceptional and it's been here for a very long time. ..enough said ...go
